New Records: Adam Zampa took 3/21 in his ten overs, scored 29 runs with the bat, and took a brilliant catch towards the back end of the game.
England suffered their 6th defeat in the World Cup, and 5th consecutive loss.
Key Match Events: Marnus Labuschagne scored 71 off 83; Cameron Green scored 47 off 52 for Australia.
Ben Stokes scored 64 off 90; Dawid Malan scored 50 off 64 for England.
Chris Woakes took 4/54 (9.3 overs); Adil Rashid took 2/38 (10 overs) for England.
Adam Zampa took 3/21 (10 overs); Pat Cummins took 2/49 (10 overs) for Australia.
Pre-Game Insights: England's World Cup 2023 journey has witnessed consistent alterations, as they have shuffled their lineup in every match.
The primary concern for Jos Buttler's side has been their batting, as they have struggled constantly, getting dismissed for 170 or fewer runs in their last three matches.
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler spoke about the disappointment of the loss, stating that they were having the same chat after the match.
Pat Cummins spoke about the team's improvement, stating that they've been getting better with each match.
Adam Zampa was awarded the Player of the Match for his sensational outing in the clash.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was a nail-biting finish, with England needing 54 more runs to win off four overs.
Cameron Green's trousers slipped while diving to save a boundary, and the video went viral.
Others: Australia won by 33 runs, and grabbed two crucial points to solidify their position at the points table with five wins in seven games played thus far.
England are now officially out of the World Cup.
